headline: Ocular Therapeutix stock news: Why positive data led to a 25% drop
summary: Investing.com -- Ocular Therapeutix (NASDAQ:OCUL) stock fell 25% Tuesday after the company reported top-line results from its Phase 3 SOL-1 superiority trial for Axpaxli in wet age-related macular degeneration (AMD). EyePoint (NASDAQ:EYPT) shares dropped 15%, while Regeneron Pharmaceuticals (NASDAQ:REGN) shares were flat.
